            <div class="b-comment">
	<a href="#" class="scroll-wrapper" name="21468"></a>
	<div class="comment" id="comment_21468">
			<div class="b-post-author">
					<div class="l-avatar">
						<a class="avatar" href="https://dou.ua/users/a.berstainer/">
							<div class="g-avatar">	<img src="https://s.dou.ua/img/avatars/40x40_anon.png" user="13862" title="a.berstainer" width="40" height="40" alt="a.berstainer" srcset="https://s.dou.ua/img/avatars/80x80_anon.png 1.1x">
</div>
							a.berstainer
						</a>
					</div>

				<span class="prof">
						
				</span>


				<a class="comment-link" href="#21468">8 сентября 2009 13:01</a>
			</div>

		<div class="l-text b-typo">
			<div><p>Since I&nbsp;can read u/r&nbsp;— in&nbsp;my&nbsp;h.o. many of&nbsp;those complaints above are coming from people who can’t manage their own risks and undertake the opportunities. As&nbsp;all know, company employs people to&nbsp;make business. Business itself&nbsp;is, usually, interesting thing, but there would be&nbsp;huge amount of&nbsp;people who makes tiny-small things done, those who manage and makes things done for bigger pieces&nbsp;— and fraction of&nbsp;those who makes things completely done, and takes responsibility of&nbsp;being successful or&nbsp;not. If&nbsp;you for some reason can’t fit yourself into any place of&nbsp;this hierarchy&nbsp;— that is&nbsp;not always a&nbsp;bad company which makes you unhappy though... quite honest as&nbsp;of&nbsp;me.<br>As&nbsp;of&nbsp;the work that you do&nbsp;and per job level that you have in&nbsp;a&nbsp;company&nbsp;— people as&nbsp;resources can be&nbsp;split on&nbsp;those who make things done, can motivate others and enjoy doing business and those who are not.... That said&nbsp;— you can be&nbsp;a&nbsp;chief of&nbsp;the chief but if&nbsp;you can’t make things done right now, here and under sun over your head, or&nbsp;you’re bored by&nbsp;what you&nbsp;do, or&nbsp;you can’t help other make their work&nbsp;— good reason to&nbsp;revise your strategy as&nbsp;of&nbsp;being a&nbsp;good employee, colleague and the asset that every company is&nbsp;looking for.</p>

<p>And If&nbsp;I&nbsp;were you&nbsp;I would trust your own feeling rather than judgments if&nbsp;people you don’t know.</p></div>
		</div>

				<a class="review-link" href="https://jobs.dou.ua/companies/epam-systems/reviews/21468/">
					Ссылка
				</a>

			<div class="sup-users">
					<span></span>
			</div>

	</div>
